[The above article by Bower et al. highlights many important issues regarding the diagnosis of diseases that present with hemorrhagic symptoms, ranging from dengue hemorrhagic fever to CCHF and Marburg/Ebola viruses. The article by Chitimia-Dobler et al. complements that human study by demonstrating the 1st detection of CCHF virus in ticks collected from animals in Sudan. There is definitely a need to build strong disease-surveillance systems that are supported by robust laboratory diagnostic capacity to guide immediate response activities as well as long-term planning. - Mod.UBA

